      <section>
        <title>Sweden</title>
        <chapter>
          <title>The least European country</title>
          <paragraph>Mainly two factors towed the Swedish economy in 2016: interest rates were kept very low by the central bank; a strong increase in public and private spending was fostered to meet the migrants emergency.</paragraph>
        </chapter>
