        <chapter>
          <paragraph>In 2014 both private and public spending rebounded, as well as fixed investment which grew the most in seven years. On the expenditure side, household consumption is the main component of GDP and accounts for 46% of its total use, followed by government consumption (26%) and gross fixed capital formation (23%). Exports of goods and services account for 45 percent of GDP while imports account for 41%, adding 4% of total GDP.</paragraph>
