        <section>
          <title>Trend on negative?</title>                                                           <!--[1-N]-->
          <chapter>                                                         <!--[0-N]-->                                                          <!--[0-1]-->
            <paragraph>On March 22nd the National Bank of Hungary decided to adopt a negative rate because it want to reach 3% inflation. Now, the state’s inflation is increasing but it’s not enough, this is the reason why it changed in negative. Many other states are thinking about negative interest rate. Is it a new tendency? What can it do for the economy situation? Is it better or worst?</paragraph>                                                           <!--[0-N]-->
            <paragraph>In 2020 Hungary is aiming to reach the inflation rate of 3% during the year.</paragraph>                                              <!--[0-N]-->
